<p>The Texas Hospital Licensing Law for General and Special Hospitals was first enacted in 1989 by the 71st Legislature. The Private Mental Hospitals and Other Mental Health Facilities Act was first enacted in 1991 by the 72nd Legislature. The Department develops rules that establish minimum standards for hospital licensing procedures; for granting, denying, suspending, and revoking a license; for licensing fees; for operation; and for requirements concerning design and construction.</p>

